'''Goutweed''' is a rare [[herb]] that is not currently used in [[Herblore]], but rather traded to [[Sanfew]] in [[Taverley]] for random herbs at a 1:1 ratio.

Goutweed is obtained in three ways:
*By sneaking past troll guards in the storeroom under [[Burntmeat]]'s kitchen during (and after) the [[Eadgar's Ruse]] quest.
*By growing from [[gout tuber]]s in a herb patch, which are obtained occasionally from the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup]] [[minigame]]. This is not recommended as gout tubers are valued at {{Coins|{{GEP|Gout tuber}}}} on the [[Grand Exchange]].
*Rare reward from [[Brambickle]] in the [[Gnome Restaurant]] [[minigame]].

It is an item required in the [[Eadgar's Ruse]], [[Dream Mentor]] and [[Dragon Slayer II]] quests. It is therefore recommended to gather at least three goutweed when you first need to get them, so that you do not have to go back to the storeroom multiple times.

==Obtaining goutweed==
{{main|Eadgar's Ruse#Getting goutweed}}
During and after [[Eadgar's Ruse]], goutweed can be freely obtained in the [[Troll Stronghold (location)|Troll Stronghold]]. The goutweed is in the storeroom and guarded by trolls that must be avoided.

<gallery>
File:Eadgar's Ruse - Goutweed map.png|How to access the goutweed
File:Troll Stronghold dungeon map.png|Map of the Troll Stronghold with the storeroom on the right
</gallery>

==Exchanging with Sanfew==
Goutweed can be traded to Sanfew in Taverley in exchange for a herb, which is rolled off the standard [[herb drop table]]. The average value of trading in one goutweed is {{Coins|{{GEP|Grimy guam leaf|32/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy marrentill|24/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy tarromin|18/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy harralander|14/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy ranarr weed|11/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy irit leaf|8/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy avantoe|6/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy kwuarm|5/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy cadantine|4/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy lantadyme|3/128}}+{{GEP|Grimy dwarf weed|3/128}} round0}}.

